article.description: Andre Lindsey took a reverse and cruised around the left side and into the end zone to take the lead as Sacramento State rallied to beat Northern Colorado 28-25 on Saturday afternoon.
article.headline: Lindsey helps Sacramento St. rally to beat N. Colorado 28-25
article.linkText: Lindsey helps Sacramento St. rally to beat N. Colorado 28-25
article.story: GREELEY, Colo. -- Andre Lindsey took a reverse and cruised around the left side and into the end zone to take the lead as Sacramento State rallied to beat Northern Colorado 28-25 on Saturday afternoon. Sacramento State (2-1) had never led until Lindsey raced in from the 39 for a 21-17 advantage with 6:23 remaining in the game. The Bears were driving on the next series when Leonard Hazewood IV sacked Keaton Mott, forcing a fumble that was recovered by Elijah Chambers. That resulted in an Elijah Dotson's 3-yard touchdown plunge five plays later. Northern Colorado (0-3) quickly responded with Mott hitting Noah Sol with an 8-yard TD pass. Mott then passed to Michael McCauley for two extra points for the final score with 1:35 remaining. The ensuing onside kick was recovered by the Hornets. Kevin Thomson threw for 244 yards and a score for Northern Colorado. Mott was 26-of-43 passing for 315 yards and two TDs. Both teams are members of the Big Sky Conference but this did not count as a conference game.
